    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Basically what was described in #2289 is that the searchBox widget will create a new input once it's initialising. If you have some input put as that selector, you could have event listeners, or value on it, all before instantSearch starts. Here we're still making a new input DOM Node, and thus not actually taking that original node in account. \r\n\r\nThe only solution I see is not having the `input` as a selector, but also a `div`, just like the other widgets.",
