  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Ok to sum up the discussion so far:\r\n - #2289 was created because it's inconsistent to tell the users they can use their input, and then force the original state on it even if it has a value itself\r\n - there is an edge case: when there are two searchboxes there is an inconsistent visual state. It happens when one of the searchbox is not providing an input with a value. This is an edge case in a context of an edge-case and we'd be happy to work on it if a user has the issue.\r\n\r\nAs a side note, this feature (using an input instead of container) is a very early one. Nowadays it can be done with the connectors. This should probably be removed in the next major version.\r\n\r\nCan we move forward with this PR @vvo @iam4x ?",
